## Coding Conventions

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode; no `any` type; define types for all Sanity documents
- Use `sanity typegen generate` to auto-generate types from schemas
- Prefer `type` for unions/intersections, `interface` for object shapes

### Astro
- Use `.astro` for static components (default)
- Use React/Vue/Svelte only for interactive islands (`client:load`, `client:visible`, `client:idle`)
- Keep frontmatter (`---`) minimal; extract logic to `lib/`

### Sanity Schemas
- One schema per file in `src/sanity/schemas/`
- Use `defineType` and `defineField` for type safety
- Add validation rules to required fields
- Include `preview` configuration for all document types

### GROQ Queries
- Centralize queries in `src/lib/sanity.ts`
- Use parameterized queries (never interpolate variables into GROQ strings)
- Project only the fields you need (avoid `...` spread in production queries)

### General
- 2-space indentation; single quotes for strings
- Early returns to reduce nesting
- Mobile-first responsive design with Tailwind CSS

## Security Requirements

**Never read, display, or include the contents of these files:**

| Category | Files / Patterns |
|----------|-----------------|
| Environment | `.env`, `.env.*`, `.env.local`, `.env.*.local` вЂ” `.env.example` is safe |
| Keys & certs | `*.key`, `*.pem`, `*.p12`, `*.pfx`, `*.crt`, `*.cer` |
| Credentials | `auth.json`, `credentials.json`, `*service-account*.json` |
| Cloud auth | `.aws/credentials`, `.aws/config`, `.azure/` |
| SSH / Git | `.ssh/`, `.git-credentials`, `.netrc` |
| Secrets | `secrets.yml`, `vault.yml`, any file with `secret` or `token` in name |

**Hard rules:**
- `PUBLIC_` prefixed env vars are exposed to the client вЂ” never use this prefix for secrets
- Sanity project ID and dataset name are safe to expose; API tokens are NOT
- Never include API keys or tokens in code examples or responses
- Verify `.gitignore` covers `.env` variants before staging

## Important Notes

- `.astro/` and `node_modules/` are generated вЂ” never edit or commit them
- Images should always use `urlFor()` helper with width/height transforms via Sanity CDN
- Use Portable Text renderer for all Sanity rich text content
- Configure Sanity webhooks to trigger Astro rebuilds on content publish
- See `CLAUDE.md` for Claude Code-specific workflow skills and the memory system
